text: Anneliese Schuh-Proxauf (10 March 1922 - 17 November 2020) was an Austrian alpine skier and tennis player. She competed in the 1948 Winter Olympics. Schuh-Proxauf was born in Innsbruck and died in the same city at the age of 98. ==References== Category:1922 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Austria Category:Sportspeople from Innsbruck Category:Austrian skiers Category:Female tennis players
